properties.description: Forming a discreet and private set of four interlocking houses set around an open courtyard, Walmer Yard is Peter Salter's only UK project. The houses now form the home of the Baylight Foundation.

properties.name: Walmer Yard

properties.description: Beautiful mausoleum in former Royal Navy cemetery, restored 1999 by the University of Greenwich. Many interesting plaques and grave stones.

properties.description: We're excited to open up our London campus as part of Open House Festival. Foster + Partners is a global studio for sustainable architecture, urbanism, engineering and design, founded by Norman Foster in 1967. With offices across the world, the practice works as a single entity that is both ethnically and culturally diverse, with people central to all our endeavours.
properties.name: Foster + Partners

properties.description: Part of Golden Lane Estate which was the first public housing to be listed. A maisonette with much of the original detailing and finishes.

properties.description: Grade II listed, built 1790. A central double door under a bracketed cornice hood, large sash windows with delicate glazing bars. Panelled interior. Curved entrance wall allowed carriages to turn in the narrow lane. Notable burial ground.

properties.description: Delightful brick and tile building inspired by the famous 1688 Meeting House at Jordans in Buckinghamshire. A simple building in a tranquil setting, reflecting the Quakers' beliefs.

UPDATED: Open daily 10.30am-4pm.

Home of the City of London's art collection, & remains of London's Roman Amphitheatre

Wooden deer sculptures overlook the Forest

properties.name: Old Royal Naval College - Queen Mary Court

Numbered amongst the UK's architectural glories and boasting 66 acres of beautiful grounds, the Royal Hospital Chelsea has been home to the iconic Army veteran community fondly known as the 'Chelsea Pensioners' since its foundation in 1692. 
The Great Hall and Chapel will not be accessible from 12.00-14.00 on Saturday 16th September due to an internal event. The remainder of the site will be open during this time. 

Visitors should note that filming will be taking place during the afternoon of Sunday 17th September. If you would like to be excluded from any filming, please let our staff and volunteers know on arrival at the site.
properties.name: Royal Hospital Chelsea, Home of the Chelsea Pensioners
